<taxonomicName box="[151,290,331,356]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Sphyrnidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Sphyrnidae</taxonomicName>
(Hammerhead sharks)
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,331,535]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
The winghead shark 
<taxonomicName authority="Cuvier, 1816" authorityName="Cuvier" authorityYear="1816" box="[439,809,367,392]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Sphyrnidae" genus="Eusphyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blochii">
<emphasis box="[439,634,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Eusphyra blochii</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cuvier" box="[651,801,367,391]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Cuvier, G. (1816) Le Regne Animal distribue d'apres son organisation pour servir de base a l'histoire naturelle des animaux et d'introduction a l'anatomie comparee. Les reptiles, les poissons, les mollusques et les annelides. Deterville, Paris." type="book" year="1816">
Cuvier, 
<number box="[743,801,367,391]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1816.0">1816</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
has been reported from the Gulf but without evidence (
<bibRefCitation author="Randall" box="[158,314,404,428]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Randall, J. E. (1986) Sharks of Arabia. Immel, London." type="book" year="1986">
Randall 
<number box="[255,314,404,428]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1986.0">1986</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Carpenter" box="[326,581,404,428]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Carpenter, K. E., Krupp, F., Jones, D. A. &amp; Zajonz, U. (1997 a) The living marine resources of Kuwait, Eastern Saudi Arabia, Bahrain, Qatar, and the United Arab Emirates. FAO, Rome." type="book" year="1997" yearSuffix="a">
Carpenter 
<emphasis box="[444,494,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[509,568,404,428]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1997.0">1997</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
), although its occurrence in the Gulf of 
<collectingCountry box="[1033,1101,404,428]" name="Oman" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Oman</collectingCountry>
near Jask is proven (
<bibRefCitation author="Blegvad" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Blegvad, H. (1944) Danish Scientific Investigations in Iran. Part III. Fishes of the Iranian Gulf. Einar Munksgaard, Copenhagen." type="book" year="1944">
Blegvad 
<number box="[151,210,439,463]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1944.0">1944</number>
, as 
<emphasis box="[257,442,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName box="[257,353,441,464]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Sphyrnidae" genus="Sphyrna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zygaena">Zygaena</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName box="[364,442,440,464]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Sphyrnidae" genus="Eusphyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blochii">blochii</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
). Reports of the smooth hammerhead shark 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[960,1360,439,464]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Sphyrnidae" genus="Sphyrna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zygaena">
<emphasis box="[960,1156,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Sphyrna zygaena</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus" box="[1173,1352,439,463]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1758) Systema Naturae, Ed. X. (Systema naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. Holmiae (Stockholm)." type="book" year="1758">
Linnaeus, 
<number box="[1295,1352,439,463]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1758.0">1758</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in the Gulf were doubted by Randall (
<number box="[514,574,476,500]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1996.0">1996</number>
), and our data support this, although a number of specimens of this species have recently been confirmed from 
<collectingCountry box="[551,619,511,535]" name="Oman" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Oman</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Henderson" box="[634,930,511,535]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Henderson, A. C. &amp; Reeve, A. J. (2011) Noteworthy elasmobranch records from Oman. African Journal of Marine Science, 33, 171 - 175." type="journal article" year="2011">
Henderson &amp; Reeve 
<number box="[870,930,511,535]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
